channel.title: JBoss Issue Tracker
channel.description: This file is an XML representation of an issue

item.title: [ENTESB-4220] Just created container immediately disappears
item.description:
Container dissappears few seconds after it's created in Hawtio but the issue isn't related to Hawtio.
This works fine on Fedora 20 but fails on Windows.

Container is created via command:

container-create-child root child_container

or via Hawtio. Result is the same.

status.description: The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.

comments.comment:
Did a quick test with latest version of JBoss Fuse 6.2.1-redhat-054 and this issue is still there

java.net.UnknownHostException: c

at sun.net.NetworkClient.doConnect(NetworkClient.java:139)
at sun.net.NetworkClient.openServer(NetworkClient.java:118)

We have to revert fix for ENTESB-3756.
New patching mechanism handles child containers better.

The problem happens only on Windows. I can revert one fix and say that ENTESB-3756 is solved by new patching mechanism rather then changes to how child containers are created.
Please do not test child containers on Windows for now.
When can I make a new test ? which release ?
Charles Moulliard If you can avoid testing child containers on Windows now, it'd be great - please test them under Linux. I should have this fixed this week.
I can't use unix machine with my partners as they all have a Window machine and we install locally JBoss Fuse Fabric to train them. Next course is planned next week

OK, so we need a fix and new perfectus build - it'll be newer than ER4.
Aileen Cunningham should I start new perfectus immediately? or await for at least few issues related to ER4 testing?

We need a patch for windows issue as soon as possible so that QE can test on windows.

We can do further patches later if other critical issues found - this way QE are testing the patch process as well.
Charles Moulliard Please use the attached fabric-core-1.2.0.redhat-621069.jar for now.
Thx. I will make a test asap.

Charles Moulliard with the single change to fabric-core, child containers are created successfully. I have only this exception (which is only related to patching and doesn't affect provisioning:
